      <title>Customizing Log Output with Seilog&#39;s IDestructuring Policy</title>
      <link>https://blog.weiwang.dev/posts/2024/customizing-log-output-with-seilog-idestructuring-policy/</link>
      <pubDate>Tue, 06 Aug 2024 13:02:35 -0400</pubDate>
      <guid>https://blog.weiwang.dev/posts/2024/customizing-log-output-with-seilog-idestructuring-policy/</guid>
      <description>&lt;p&gt;Serilog is a powerful logging library for .NET that allows deep customization of how objects are represented in structured logs. One such customization point is &lt;code&gt;IDestructuringPolicy&lt;/code&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2 id=&#34;what-is-idestructuringpolicy&#34;&gt;What is &lt;code&gt;IDestructuringPolicy&lt;/code&gt;?&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;code&gt;IDestructuringPolicy&lt;/code&gt; is an interface in Serilog that lets you control how specific objects are transformed into structured log data. This is especially useful when you want to:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Omit sensitive fields (e.g., passwords, tokens)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Rename properties&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Format output differently&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
